						04/04/2012 02:15:45 AM MDT</p><div id="articleBody" class="articleBody">Remember when it was just fried chicken, mashed potatoes and coleslaw? Now KFC has a handful of chicken styles and more than a dozen sides &#x2014; including salads. Be smart with your choices &#x2014; they seem to be kind of obvious here, though.<p>
<b>THE SHOWDOWN:</b></p><p>
<b>Extra Crispy Chicken (thigh and drumstick)</b></p><p>
Calories: 340 (thigh) and 150 (drumstick)</p><p>
Fat: 24g (thigh) and 10g (drumstick)</p><p>
Cholesterol:  80mg (thigh) and 55mg (drumstick)</p><p>
Fiber: 0g</p><p>
Protein: 20g (thigh) and 12g (drumstick)</p><p>
Mashed Potatoes with Gravy</p><p>
Calories: 120</p><p>
Fat: 4g</p><p>
Cholesterol: 0mg</p><p>
Fiber: 1g</p><p>
Protein: 2g</p><p>
Wild Cherry Pepsi (20 oz.)</p><p>
Calories: 230</p><p>
Total calories: 840 &#x2014; add the 180-calorie biscuit, 1,020</p><p>
VS.</p><p>
<b>Grilled Chicken (thigh and drumstick)</b></p><p>
Calories: 170 (thigh) and 90 (drumstick)</p><p>
Fat: 10g (thigh) 4g (drumstick)</p><p>
Cholesterol: 90mg (thigh) 60mg (drumstick)</p><p>
Fiber: 0g</p><p>
Protein: 19g (thigh) 13g (drumstick)</p><p>
House Side Salad with Marzetti Light Italian Dressing</p><p>
Calories: 30</p><p>
Fat: 0.5g</p><p>
Cholesterol: 0mg</p><p>
Fiber: 1g</p><p>
Protein: 1g</p><p>
Diet Sierra Mist</p><p>
Calories: 0</p><p>
Total calories: 290, plus the 180 calorie biscuit, 470.</p><p>
<b>THE LOWDOWN: </b>Grilled makes all the difference. What crispy really is, is flour and empty, deep-fried calories. Grilled chicken has a little less bulk but it's just as tasty. The thing is, they all cost the same. Be smart with your money: a bucket (8) of grilled chicken pieces is 1,120 calories, original chicken is about 1,700 calories and an extra crispy bucket comes in at 2,380 calories.</p><p>
